  "issue_title": "genie-core chat fails through genie-ai-runtime while health reports connected",
  "issue_body": "## Context\n\nAfter PR #70 and PR #72 were merged and deployed, `genie-core` now stays up under systemd and the web/dashboard surfaces load. However, the web control UI still cannot get a chat reply through `genie-core`.\n\n`genie-core` health reports the LLM as connected:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sf http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/health\n```\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\":\"ok\",\n  \"llm\":\"connected\",\n  \"llm_backend\":\"genie-ai-runtime\",\n  \"model_family\":\"Qwen\"\n}\n```\n\n`genie-ctl status` also reports core is up:\n\n```text\nGovernor:  night_a mode\nMemory:    3093 MB available\nUptime:    1h 4m\nCore:      ok\nRadio:     disabled\nWebSearch: enabled (duckduckgo)\n```\n\nThe dashboard at port 3080 loads, but its Services table reports:\n\n```text\ncore  Healthy  80ms\nllm   Connection refused (os error 111)  0ms\n```\n\nAnd a direct `genie-core` chat request through the web/API path fails:\n\n```bash\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/chat \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"X-Genie-Origin: dashboard\" \\\n  -d '{\"message\":\"Say hello from the GeniePod web UI in one short sentence.\"}'\n```\n\nResponse:\n\n```json\n{\"error\":\"chat: genie-ai-runtime 0: \"}\n```\n\n## Why this is likely a GenieClaw issue\n\nThe `genie-ai-runtime` service itself had previously been validated directly:\n\n- `/health` on port 8080 returned `status: ok`\n- `/v1/chat/completions` returned a valid answer: `Hello from GeniePod!`\n- Qwen3 model weights stayed warm after issue #69 / PR #70\n\nSo the failure appears to be in the GenieClaw integration path between:\n\n- `genie-core /api/chat`\n- `genie-core`'s `genie-ai-runtime` OpenAI-compatible adapter\n- health/dashboard service checks for the LLM backend\n\n## Suspicions to investigate\n\n- `genie-core` health may check one endpoint successfully while chat posts to a different URL/path or port.\n- The `genie-ai-runtime` adapter may not parse the runtime's OpenAI-compatible response correctly and may surface an empty status/body as `genie-ai-runtime 0: `.\n- `genie-health` / dashboard may still be checking the old llama.cpp service or a stale URL, causing `llm Connection refused` even when the active backend is `genie-ai-runtime`.\n- There may be a mismatch between `[services.llm]` config, `genie-core` adapter URL construction, and dashboard health probe logic.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `curl http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/chat` returns a normal assistant response when `[services.llm].backend = \"genie_ai_runtime\"`.\n- The port 3000 web chat UI displays the assistant reply.\n- The port 3080 dashboard no longer shows `llm Connection refused` when the active LLM backend is `genie-ai-runtime` and healthy.\n- `genie-core /api/health`, `genie-ctl status`, dashboard service health, and direct runtime `/health` agree on the active LLM backend state.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-18T05:40:25.000Z",
